cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.RO 

The paper discusses neural networks and swarm optimization, which are both subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on the cognitive abilities of these architectures suggests a connection to cognitive science (cs.NE). The discussion of multiple scales and their relationship to computation and adaptation suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY). The comparison of different architectures suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of realistic biological models suggests a connection to robotics (cs.RO).
